Isolates are similar to threads in Unix
Does not share memory like threads
Communication between Isolates are done through messages

A Flutter app is Single Isolate thread App.
It has its own event loop and Queue.

Isolates helps to execute code in a different process.

If we want to execute a heavy operation and doesn't want to block the 
UI thread, we need to use isolates.

Two ways to use isolates

1. Using the compute function.
2. Using SendPort and ReceivePort for message passing.




